You removed an EC2 instance block from your .tf file but did not run terraform destroy. You now run terraform apply. What will Terraform do?

If you remove an EC2 instance block from your Terraform (.tf) file but do not run terraform destroy, and then execute terraform apply, Terraform will plan to destroy the EC2 instance. 
This happens because Terraform's state file still contains the resource, but your configuration (.tf files) no longer defines it. 
During terraform apply, Terraform recognizes that the resource is "managed" but now missing from your desired state, 
so it schedules it for deletion from your AWS account and removes it from the state file as well
